		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ok, so ran into my first problem. I'm trying to create some triangle-like drums using the looped noise of the nes, and Here's the code I'm using. <br /><br />; let's try some drums...<br />@v2 = {15 8 8 8 7 7 7 6 6 6 5 5 5 4 3 2 1 }0 ; open triangle<br />@v3 = {12 6 5 4 2 1 0} ; mute triangle<br />D o1 l16 @1<br />D [[@v2 d8 @v3 d d ]4 ]8<br /><br />the line with the @1 in it is flagged with an error, even though I thought @1 on the noise channel would change it to looped noise? If I removed the @1, it works fine, but of course I only get regular noise with that. any ideas?<br />this is with ppmck 9aEx5.3

		

		</td>
	</tr>
