	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You're going to be a bit constrained with using the envelope channel for pitches; the sunsoft 5b runs at (effectively) ≈½ the speed of e.g. the ZX Spectrum or Atari ST's sound.<br />In practice, you'll have something like the bottom octave or so of well-tuned notes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


